Version | Date | Expert in charge | Changes applied
01.00.00 | yyyy-mm-dd | Siemens Digital Industries | First released version
Notes for things to be done:
Migration to S7-1200 G2 and optimization

Comment.MultiLanguageText:
This block is able to execute commands for some MC commands like MoveVelocity and MoveAbsolute. It was created with teh 1200G2 in mind to provide a Light weight version of the LBC_AxisControl. To use more advanced functionalities like CamIn and GearIn, it needs to be done either with the additional functions LBC blocks of directly with the MC commands.
This block used as inspiration/base the LAxisCtrl and LAxisBasics for the motion control (MC) operation.
To keep the Block lightweight with good performance but still with good diagnosis options, under the `commandConfiguration` there is the `readValues` UDT. The `readValues` gives the option to enable and disable the reading of of the current warning word, error word etc. The enabling of the different read values options do have an inpact on the performance of the block.
